eading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Acrok Video Converter makes an appearance in our review of the best <a href=\"https://www.tomsguide.com/us/convert-dvds-to-digital-files,review-4813.html\">Blu-ray to iPad rippers</a>. However, we had several concerns with this program. First, the program is very touchy. It crashed numerous times, even during simple tasks. Second, the preview window never worked, so our recommendation is that you know the exact number of the file you want to convert.","At first glance, this Blu-ray to iPad converter is a simple, intuitive program. It loads disc contents quickly. It bypasses copy protections found on commercial discs. It has several preprogrammed iPad conversion profiles. You can start a conversion in about three clicks. Each hour of video content takes about two hours to convert. And the video file produced is perfectly watchable on your iPad.  These are the key attributes we looked for in our review of the best Blu-ray to iPad converters.","However, the program is extremely unstable. Each time we tried to access a tool outside simply converting a file, the application hesitated and quickly crashed. During our testing, Acrok Video Converter froze no less than five times. Sometimes it simply shut down; other times we had to force quit the application because it became unresponsive. There were even times we had to restart our test machine in order to get the program to relaunch after a crash.","Our test video file synced to iPad with no problems and the video quality was adequate. During our examination we noticed some slight pixilation and compression artifact. We also noticed that the audio was marginally out of sync. You may not notice, but if you do, you won’t be able to watch your video without being distracted by it.","Additionally, this program fails in a major way when it comes to its customization features. It technically has all the tools necessary to trim and crop footage on your Blu-ray disc and adjust the picture’s contrast, brightness and saturation. However, in practice, these tools are nonfunctional. During our tests, we were unable to use any of the tools under the Edit tab of this application. It simply ceased functioning then crashed.","The program performs better when you&#39;re adjusting the output settings. Fine-tuning video properties such as bitrate, frame rate, resolution and aspect ratio all work well. As long as you’re okay with ripping an entire Blu-ray track or disc, this program can meet your most basic needs."]},"id":"36911e46-3249-413a-9b42-b77d50010077","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"8d0dec94-e9bc-49de-9dcb-78c100f244c8","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["If you’re going to use this application to convert your Blu-ray discs for playback on your iPad, you have to act fast. Launch the program, pick your model of iPad, select the file you want and click convert. Any activity outside of this almost certainly results in the application failing."]},"id":"41c23679-6d73-4e56-95ae-0dfedd795629","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_64956","url":"/acrok-video-converter-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"j-d-chadwick","url":"/author/j-d-chadwick","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"J.D. Chadwick","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"Q2hDFnLxcyQrSWYJF8ZLKH","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2015-05-19T14:24:04Z","datePublished":"2015-05-19T14:24:04Z","name":"Acrok Video Converter","synopsis":"Acrok Video Converter makes an appearance in our review of the best Blu-ray to iPad rippers. However, we had several concerns with this program. First, the program is very touchy. It crashed numerous times, even during simple tasks.","review":{"rating":77,"verdict":"This program is capable of making a successful Blu-ray to iPad conversion, but that doesn&#8217;t mean you should buy it.","pros":["This software successfully made a file that would sync and pl